{'en': {'shortDesc': 'desktop planetarium for KDE', 'pkgName': 'kstars', 'longDesc': u'KStars is a desktop planetarium for KDE, depicting an accurate graphical simulation of the night sky, from any location on Earth, at any date and time. The display includes 130,000 stars, 13,000 deep-sky objects, all 8 planets, the Sun and Moon, and thousands of comets and asteroids.  It includes tools for astronomical calculations and can control telescopes and cameras.\n\nThis package is part of the KDE education module.'}}